<a name="Overview"></a><h2> <span class="mw-headline">Overview</span></h2>
<p>Scripts open a new avenue for asynchronous communication between learners in virtual environments. Scripts advance MUVE's beyond the realm of decorative chat rooms to scaffold more thoughful student interaction with the virtual environment. Scripts also make manipulable simulations possible.
</p>
<ul><li> <a href="http://www.cs.ualberta.ca/~script" class="external text" title="http://www.cs.ualberta.ca/~script" rel="nofollow">ScriptEase</a> "AI scripting... model is pattern template based, allowing designers to quickly build complex behaviors without doing explicit programming." Developed at the University of Alberta for Bioware's Neverwinter Nights.
</li></ul>
<ul><li> Neverwinter Nights <a href="http://nwn.bioware.com/builders/sctutorial.html" class="external text" title="http://nwn.bioware.com/builders/sctutorial.html" rel="nofollow">scripting tutorials</a>.
</li></ul>
<a name="Interactive_Scripts_for_Teaching"></a><h2> <span class="mw-headline">Interactive Scripts for Teaching</span></h2>
<a name="Agents"></a><h3> <span class="mw-headline">Agents</span></h3>
<p><a href="/wiki/index.php?title=Linden_AIML" title="Linden AIML">Linden AIML</a> chat bot by Azrael Baphomet and Luciftias Neurocam
</p><p><a href="/wiki/index.php?title=SL_Tour_Guide" title="SL Tour Guide">SL Tour Guide</a> bot by Wandering Yaffle
</p><p><a href="/wiki/index.php?title=Flashcard_learning_system" title="Flashcard learning system">Flashcard learning system</a> collaborative learning agent
</p>
<a name="Assessment"></a><h3> <span class="mw-headline">Assessment</span></h3>
<p><a href="/wiki/index.php?title=SL_Survey_Script" title="SL Survey Script">SL Survey Script</a> by Eloise Pasteur. Concept by Jeremy Kemp, edits by Baba Kofi Weusijana.
</p>
